-- Los Angeles Lakers' Kobe Bryant Recovering From Arthroscopic Knee Surgery
-- Nancy Kercheval
-- 2010-07-24T02:09:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-24/los-angeles-lakers-kobe-bryant-recovering-from-arthroscopic-knee-surgery.html

          
          
             Los Angeles Lakers guard  Kobe Bryant 
is recovering from arthroscopic surgery on his right knee, the
National Basketball Association team said.  
 The two-time defending Finals Most Valuable Player
underwent surgery last week.  
 “Bryant is currently undergoing rehab and is expected to
be fully recovered prior to the start of the Lakers’ training
camp on Sept. 25,” the team said on its website.  
 Bryant, 31, averaged 27 points per game last season, and
29.2 points per game during the playoffs.  
